article.headline: UC Riverside 91, Cal Poly-SLO 57
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. -- Kyle Austin scored 24 points to lead UC Riverside past Cal Poly 91-57 Friday. Austin, a transfer from Southern California, went 9-of-18 from the floor as the Highlanders (8-4, 1-0 Big West) outscored the Mustangs 49-19 in the second half. Cal Poly led 36-33 late in the first half before UC Riverside went on a 23-4 run to break the game open. At one point during the run, Cal Poly went 9:55 without a field goal. UC Riverside led by as many as 37 late in the second half. Riverside's Javon Borum scored 19 points on 7-of-12 shooting, including 5-of-7 from 3-point range. Freshman Konner Veteto added 15 points and Aaron Scott had 11 for the Highlanders, who improved to 6-0 at home this season and are having their best start since moving to Division I in 2001-01. Titus Shelton scored 17 points for the Mustangs (3-8, 0-1).
